The paper deals with improving style similarity metrics for 3D shapes, which is a problem that falls under computer graphics (cs.GR) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also explores clustering and user-guided learning, which are topics that fall under machine learning (cs.AI, cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses applications such as style-based similarity search and scene composition, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM).
